    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-05-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-05-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="89"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d89">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">639.003/55</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Russell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 27, 1919</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 288</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department is informed of an intention on the
                    part of the Military Government to revise the tariff in Santo Domingo.<note
                        n="50" xml:id="d89fn50">See report of Apr. 17, of the Military Governor of
                        Santo Domingo, <ref target="#pg_99">p. 99</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>You are requested to report on the circumstances which might have the effect of
                    necessitating a change in the tariff rates, and to make such comment as you may
                    be disposed for use by the Department in passing upon the new schedules.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Acting Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
